	<Title>
		Are you wearing your bike helmet correctly?
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;A bike helmet works only if you wear it correctly. A helmet should cover the top of your forehead without tilting forward or backward. Fasten the chin strap just below your chin. The straps should form a V shape under each ear. Use the foam sizing pads that came with the helmet to ensure a snug fit.&lt;/p.
	</Body>
